            </group_id_list>
            <groups_desc>Assuming a common standard deviation of 1.1%, 60 evaluable participants would provide 93% power to detect a statistically significant –1.0% difference in change from baseline HbA1c at Week 12 between ranolazine and placebo (2-sided alpha = 0.05). 80 participants were randomized to ensure at least 60 evaluable participants.</groups_desc>
